featured_reviews.review_id:
The Second Jyotirlinga Shree Mallikarjun 
This jyotirlinga is believed to provide you blessings if you are struggling with luck as well as in marriage.
This is the jyotirlinga of Vigro (Kanya) zodiac sign.
Lord Murugan came here when he got angry on Goddess Parvati and then Lord Mahadeva and Goddess Parvati followed him here.
Goddess Parvati is in the form of Bhramarambhadevi which is also a Shaktipeeth among the 52 shaktipeethas.

The meaning of the deity name is as follows -

Mallika- Parvati
Arjun - Mahadev

There are 5 ways of darshan for per person:
1. Free Darshan
2. Sheeghra Darshan Rs150 (fast)
3. Atti Sheeghra Darshan Rs300 (more fast)
4. Alkankara Darshan Rs500
5. Sparsha Darsha Rs500 (not available daily check temple official website for more details)

Sri Bhramaramba Mallikarjuna Seamy temple is very beautiful with full of positive vibes. It's one of the Jyothirlingas out of 12. Temple premises is well maintained and organised for devotees. It may take 30 mins to max 2 hours for Dharshan depending upon the seasons. There are facilities for early darshan also for 300 rupees.
Mobile and other electronics devices are not allowed inside the temple. There are facilities to keep mobile phone and luggage's safely.
Daily prasadam is there for devotees. It will take 4-5 hours to reach from Hyderabad by private vehicle. There are many hotels are for accommodation. Better to carry umbrella if you are coming in summer or rainy seasons.

Sri Mallikarjuna Jyotirlinga is situated on Sri Shail mountain in Andhra Pradesh. Here Mother Parvati is seated as Mallika and Lord Shiva is seated as Arjun...
The journey started with a flight from Delhi to Hyderabad, then a bus leaves from Majibs Mahatma Gandhi Bus Stand in Hyderabad for Srisailam Jyotirlinga. Auto fare from Kachiguda to MBBS ranges between Rs100 to Rs180 while bus fare is Rs20 per person. Fare from MGBS to Srisailam is Rs500 per passenger and the time taken is minimum 5-6 hours.. .
Try to visit the temple early in the morning. The maximum time for darshan is 1 to 2 hours.
Auto fare for five temples there is local site, local temple which is famous..
Their fare is Rs 120 per passenger or if there are five people, you can reserve it for Rs 600. The 5 temples they show include Sakshi Ganapati, Panchdhara, Hatkeshwar Temple, Shikhareshwar Mahadev, and Lalita Devi Temple...
Other famous places there are Patal Ganga-1km, Srisailam Dam-25km, Malela Theertham Falls-55km, Srisailam Sanctuary-30km, Akkamahadevi Caves-550rs per person child ka-440rs...
Patalganga is 1 kilometer away, where you can also go by ropeway. The fare for both sides is Rs 80 for a person and Rs 60 for a child.

featured_reviews.review_id:
What a peaceful and divine experience. Srisailam has the jyotirling and shaktipeeth both. This makes this place more sacred.

Things to note before visiting this place.

(1) Srisailam is 200kms from Hyderabad. By road it will take nearly 5 hours to reach. Plan to leave your place early.

(2) Before entering into the Srisailam, must visit Sakshi Ganpati temple. It comes before the Srisailam city. Local believes that if you don't visit this temple, your visit to the Srisailam will be uncountable. Sakshi Ganpati temple is small and mostly remains crowded.

(3) Book your stay in advance as there are very limited options available in Srisailam and if you ask local, they will add their charges also. We paid 500 extra per room.

(4) Not much food options are there but ganesh food court is a good option to have breakfast, lunch and dinner. You'll get dosa, idly, vada, veg meal, fruit bowl, pizza, icecream and tea-coffee.

(5) Quick darshan passes are there if you want to avoid the long long queue. 150 for Sigra darshan (1-1.5 hour), 300 for Ati-sigra darshan (30-35 mins) and 500 for Sparsh darshan (10-15 mins). Sparsh darshan will give you the chance to touch jyotirling. With these passes also you will not get much time to do darshan. These tickets are only useful for jyotirling darshan. Shaktipeeth entrance comes after jyotirling visit. If you want to go for a sparsh darshan ticket, plan to book it in advance. They have very limited tickets. Also confirm the time for the same.

(6) Traditional cloths are compulsory only if your are going for a pooja. Still some of the clothings are not acceptable. Please visit the temple site to check the list.

(7) Apart from the temple, other places can be visited. Shivaji temple, Nandi temple, Patal ganga & Akka Mahadevi caves.

(8) For patal ganga, boat ride will be there which takes you to the centre of the Srisailam dam reservoir. Nothing much is there to do.

(9) Visit to the Akka Mahadevi caves takes more than 8 hours. If you have a enough than only plan to visit it.

The story and belief behind this is the lord Ganesha keeps regular account of pilgrims of their visit to srisailam.
This temple is about 3 km from the main temple.
We went by walk but better take auto. You can visit in the morning 6 am to  night at 9 pm. Must visit this temple otherwise your mallikarjuna darshan will not be counted...

featured_reviews.review_id: It is a must visit destination of Srisailam pilli gyms this Temple is dedicated to Lord Ganapathi or Vinayaka. The lord will hold a book and pen in his hands. There is a Belief in the pilgrims that Lord Vinayaka is going to write the name of the pilgrims who have visited the Sri Sailam Temple full stop and he is going to convey this message to Lord Shiva. That's why every pilgrim who went to Sri Sailam will visit this Temple as a proof to Lord Shiva. this temple is on the highway itself. We will see this temple on our way to Lord Mallikarjuna Swamy Temple full stop there is a plenty of parking facility here. Nearby shops are also available here where we can buy cool drinks fruits biscuits etc. Homams are conducted at this Temple. We have to book the tickets for homam/ Archana. Every bilgram will book Archana tickets here in this temple. then Pujari will read our gotta namas front of Lord Vinayaka it's only Rs 10 ticket. There is a little crowd in this Temple but the security people are clearing the crowded fastly and making Darshan arrangement as much early as they can full stop there is a lot of place inside the temple to sit in front of Vinayaka full stop the lord will blesses with positive energy and good wives in our life. Every one must visit this Temple if they go to Srisailam. it's a famous destination for Srisailam visitors
